{
  "text": "The topographic map of the body surface in S1 is highly ordered, with the lateral skin surface and medial skin surface represented from medial to lateral aspects, and digits and heel represented from rostral to caudal aspects respectively [CITATION_1] ) (see also METHODS). However, not all receptive fields conformed to this topography, especially in each of the two sciatic nerve crush groups. For example, a receptive field on the heel, which is typically recorded in caudal S1, was occasionally located in rostral S1, where digits are typically represented. While these displaced receptive fields were infrequent it seemed that an index of topographic order was needed to quantify any systematic change in topography as a result of sciatic nerve crush.",
